title: iHARP Sea Level Anomaly Detection
description: Conducted data preprocessing and cleaning on large geospatial datasets, transforming raw tide gauge data into a structured format for analysis. Designed and implemented a Random Forest Classifier to predict anomalies with a focus on model performance.

title: U.S. Power Outage Predictions & Analysis
description: Analyzed 1,500+ power outages over 15 years to identify trends in weather, population, and state factors. Built an interactive website to share findings with non-technical users.

title: Geospatial Data Analysis for Healthcare Education in Children
description: Utilized data monetization to develop SharpKids, a UI prototype and product designed to integrate with Sharp Healthcare's existing app. Focuses on exploring geospatial data and analysis to provide healthcare education to children across San Diego and the nation.

title: Missing Department Administrator Analysis
description: Utilized Microsoft Excel and SAP Concur Reporting to clean and analyze data on over 200 missing department administrators. Improved reporting efficiency in SAP Concur.

title: Merchant Category Code Mapping
description: Utilized Microsoft Excel to map over 500 MCCs to over 100 Expense Types. Streamlined choosing Expense Types in the launch of Concur 2.0.

title: Meteorite Landing Data Analysis
description: Leveraged NASA's Open Data Portal to analyze global meteorite landing patterns. Applied statistical methods including hypothesis testing, random sampling, and Total Variation Distance to identify meteor fall locations.

title: Taylor Swift Song Analysis
description: Developed data visualizations using matplotlib.pyplot to illustrate musical trends and listener preferences. Created a song recommendation system based on audio feature similarity.
